But inflation undermined the growth spurt by a major devaluation in 2002.
For this reason, Cristina Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez may want to rejoin Argentina financially with the rest of the world.
Earlier this year, the government signed an agreement with securities holders who had rejected the country’s previous debt restructuring in 2001.
Now Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez seems to be pushing for an agreement with the Paris Club donors, to whom she owes about $6.7 billion.
The Kirchners had always rejected a review by the IMF, as usual elsewhere.
