It is not known whether Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez will be politically active after the end of her term of office, even without the support of her husband.
If so, it needs the support of the middle class, which has largely enough of Kirchnerism.
When the Argentines return from their summer vacation in March, the wave of sympathy that has been given to them will be squeezed.
If she wants to win another election, she has to decide whether to quietly cancel many of her husband’s political decisions.
