“They are in good condition.”
"They were returned to their rightful owners."
Whitmore did not provide any precise information on the location of the dogs or the circumstances that led to their discovery.
"The investigation is still ongoing."
“We don’t want to say that anymore,” Whitmore said.
"We're following some traces."
The dog owners, Kristina Rickard and David Peek, were not available for information on Thursday.
They received their two dogs on Wednesday afternoon at a district animal shelter in Downey.
Representatives of the sheriff found the van and the two dogs at different locations in Compton.
The Akitas - Trace, a 3-year-old male, and Didi, a 10-month-old bitch - were unharmed, according to the authorities.
