Justice Department prosecutors have acquitted Senator John Ensign of the allegations brought against him after his affair with a former electoral assistant and his attempt to get her husband to lobby, the senator’s lawyers announced on Wednesday.
This decision ended the most serious lawsuit against Senator Ensign, the Republican from Nevada, until the scandal, which made headlines nationwide and shocked his career, he was considered a possible Republican presidential candidate for 2012.
