Both the police and the State Security Service are blackmailing high protection funds so that they can maintain their expensive standard of living in Moscow.
They collect money not only from legitimate businesses, but also from organized criminal gangs.
Every layer of bureaucracy—what Prime Minister Vladimir Putin has called the “vertical of authority”—takes its share of the money that heads up.
The memo, sent to Washington under the name of Ambassador John Beyrle, was published on his homepage on Tuesday by WikiLeaks.
